![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/bannernewsletter.png)
Welcome to September's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute, Roche and beyond.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FrvVipvhg6EEPYW_0sKDiOQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352866868207%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=kIw9OzJ8oSq15JgSKmujK5sGnak671vtahdjAzJa6Vg%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F7qCMi5gH_WCEuL3N_Qdqmg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352866868207%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=VjbQWmWD8Li6ugKCXADa8upnO2ejVsPjmVSE5XanpSM%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care.**

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FivC5-wgAgFF8wO2NhEQ4JA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352866868207%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Vmb1EWuKekJidQt5XYiilOr309MZ%2FIjMBRnlAi429jA%3D&reserved=0).

### **Knowledge Share Series Event: Natural Language Processing in Health**

**26 September 2023**

Join us for our [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FuvsFE5nFuqh2VIWaqwPcLg&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352867024458%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ZZ3SdovtwjyR23wIG28hZXp7eK624QDsf0DKBandsYw%3D&reserved=0). Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and the wider scientific community to share different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

September's event is on the 26th and this month our theme will be Natural Language Processing in Health. We'll be exploring the potential this approach may have to enable data-driven decision making, generate new insights and ultimately improve patient care.

We will be hearing from Lucia Schmidt, Postdoctoral Researcher in the Data Science Team at Roche and Trisevgeni Papakonstantinou, a PhD student in the UCL's Causal Cognition Lab and Turing Enrichment Student. You can register for the event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FCUvZ-2rwH1cpFRS-MF0VUw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352867024458%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=IWMSyA1JPfBXJAb6os%2B4ORcDM3CQTRYD9npdsg4CnHk%3D&reserved=0).

You can catch-up on previous recordings of our events at our [YouTube channel](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FeGwJFyQT8N-5E6l-YQzUHw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352867024458%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=9I00Zm3oYigFzIOABkKbFGeNVtj4%2F7a6bjjhcvwUXQo%3D&reserved=0).

### Turing Theory and Methods Challenge Fortnights in Data Science and AI 2024

The Theory and Methods Challenge Fortnights bring together experts from the Turing University Network and other institutions worldwide to join forces for a multi-day research event on a specific theoretical or methodological challenge. Applications are now open for challenge proposals from across the Turing research community. Researchers not formally affiliated with the Turing Institute can also submit proposals, as long as they have a Turing affiliate as a Co-I. There will be two events awarded, and each event will involve 8 to 14 days of focused research. They can be held at locations across the Turing University Network or at the Institute's offices in the British Library, London. More info and how to submit [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPVFEMzRxV2x6V1dhbmwzTjRhT3VBSUo3Wml3bWRjSUd5QnNTcm9mSjgyVjdhWFdYZTFodnRETUNOQzdsS01jWjImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi0wMzlmMzBhZDlmYjQ0Mzk4YTk2MTUxNmJjZDBkZTUyNSZlc2lkPTE1NjcyNTIxLTVjNTktZWUxMS1iZTZmLTYwNDViZGQxMzU5ZCJ9%2FCJsqfW8Ux52jIBmAhJHLKQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352867024458%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=b8Ii%2B%2FZxaUuH6MNCGIntIj0Ic%2FTZoLcV9L%2BuUaVDQ5E%3D&reserved=0).

### Digital Health AI and Data

**30-31 October 2023**

### European Molecular Biology Laboratory (EMBL) Symposium: AI and Biology

**12-15 March 2024**

## Publication of the Month
![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/patrick-tomasso-oaqk7qqnh_c-unsplash2.jpg)

**Conformal Prediction with Missing Values**

September's publication of the month is from EDF France researcher Margaux Zaffran and colleagues, which looks at conformal prediction with missing values in the covariates -- a setting that brings new challenges to uncertainty quantification. The paper can be found on arXiv [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPVFEMzRxV2x6V1dhbmwzTjRhT3VBSUo3Wml3bWRjSUd5QnNTcm9mSjgyVjdhWFdYZTFodnRETUNOQzdsS01jWjImcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi0wMzlmMzBhZDlmYjQ0Mzk4YTk2MTUxNmJjZDBkZTUyNSZlc2lkPTE1NjcyNTIxLTVjNTktZWUxMS1iZTZmLTYwNDViZGQxMzU5ZCJ9%2FftD1YlAOaL9hjpv7SMI_eA&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7Ce454b5f1233744ad3cc008dbbdb3f5ad%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C638312352867180734%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=u0eSGEVZehz5Dwq7sHdlvPR%2B%2BNzfpvQUHD4zu5YL2FI%3D&reserved=0).
